</div><div class="t m14d x46 h4 yc06 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">11. Evidence of new birth and stable </div><div class="t m7d3 x95 h4 yee2 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">character. Rom. 5:21; Ps. 15:1-5. </div><div class="t m3c1 x46 h4 yd0d ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">12. Makes us acceptable to God. </div><div class="t m76e x95 h4 y548 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Acts 10:35. </div><div class="t m3e7 x46 h4 y102a ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">13. Brings peace and assurance. </div><div class="t mb91 x95 h4 y109f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Isa. 32:17. </div><div class="t m186 xab h71 yaf8 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">VI. Counsel to Seek Righteousness </div><div class="t m2b4 x46 h4 yae3 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">14. Hunger and thirst for. Matt. 5:6. </div><div class="t m100c x5c h71 yf4b ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THE LESSON </div><div class="t md9a x29 h71 y4b7 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Introduction: The Source and </div><div class="t mab0 x4e h71 y89c ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Definition of Righteousness </div><div class="t m1770 x73 h6 yc85 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In </div><div class="t m904 x5f h4 yc85 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">this first lesson we study briefly the </div><div class="t m637 x18 h4 yf55 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">subject of righteousness in general. We dis-</div><div class="t m111 x18 h4 ye3a ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">cover that God is the only source of right-</div><div class="t ma6a x18 h4 yd83 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">eousness and that man has no righteousness </div><div class="t m84a x18 h4 yc10 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of his own. We learn how much depends </div><div class="t m3ee x18 h4 y12e0 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">upon acquiring God&apos;s righteousness. We </div><div class="t m2ec x18 h4 yd4d ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">understand that righteousness is the op- </div><div class="t m1bd x8 h4 yd65 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">posite of sinfulness. We study several defi-</div><div class="t m656 x8 h4 ydbc ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">nitions which are vitally necessary to our </div><div class="t m233 x8 h4 y14ba ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">understanding of our objectives. Having </div><div class="t m1ad xab h4 y114d ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">studied the counsel given us to seek right-</div><div class="t m1c8 x8 h4 yc85 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">eousness most earnestly, we find that the </div><div class="t m182 x8 h4 yf55 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">gift of righteousness is received through </div><div class="t mb27 x8 h4 ye3a ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ, for He is our righteousness. </div><div class="t m719 x9 h4 y82e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What is the meaning of the word &quot;right-</div><div class="t m61c xab h4 yc10 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">eousness&quot;? It would be well to dwell upon </div><div class="t m304 x8 h4 y14e5 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the following definitions until we are able to </div><div class="t m85e x8 h4 y1286 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">see how they are related to one another: </div><div class="t m1f5 xb0 h4 y1070 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">[ 4 ] </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
